    {
      "id": "github-document-view",
      "type": "document-view",
      "label": "Document View",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1700,
        "y": 150
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "GitHub",
        "localTitle": "GitHub",
        "publishedTitle": "GitHub",
        "purpose": "Compose the dedicated GitHub overview into one readable document surface.",
        "titleSourceNodeId": "github-title",
        "typeSourceNodeId": "github-type",
        "audience": "Reader",
        "status": "active",
        "viewRole": "document",
        "viewKind": "display",
        "exposedAuthority": "consume-view",
        "runtimeExposed": false,
        "partNodeIds": [
          "github-title",
          "github-intro",
          "github-hybrid",
          "github-workflows",
          "github-usage",
          "github-boundaries",
          "github-reference-migration",
          "github-reference-beta",
          "github-annotation",
          "github-summary",
          "github-reference-repo-setup"
        ],
        "documentOrder": [
          "github-title",
          "github-intro",
          "github-hybrid",
          "github-workflows",
          "github-usage",
          "github-boundaries",
          "github-reference-migration",
          "github-reference-beta",
          "github-annotation",
          "github-summary",
          "github-reference-repo-setup"
        ],
        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,252,245,0.99), rgba(255,248,235,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(146,64,14,0.16);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(180,83,9,0.10);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;min-width:0;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#b45309;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 28px/1.12 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;word-break:break-word;\">GitHub</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(180,83,9,0.1);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#9a3412;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.45), rgba(245,158,11,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">Current GitHub overview for Twilite: browser-first navigation for everyone, authoring and publish controls for signed-in paid users, and explicit save and access state when a graph moves toward GitHub.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Introduction</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite's GitHub surface is now split more intentionally across durable browser chrome and paid authoring controls. A graph can open at a `github://...` address while document identity, save destination, and installation-scoped repo access stay explicit instead of collapsing into one vague GitHub state.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">A clearer GitHub model</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The integration gets easier to trust when five concerns stay separate: document identity, browse path, save target, installation access, and local checkout context. Workspace defaults still matter, but they are advisory. Actual repo visibility comes from the selected GitHub App installation, while branch-aware work still depends on local git context when the connector is not the right authority.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">What you can do today</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Current flows support opening a graph by `github://...`, browsing from the address bar and browser chrome, selecting a concrete installation, repository, branch, and path destination, and saving back through the GitHub App commit route when authoring is enabled. The status surfaces make it easier to tell what document is open, where the next write is pointed, and whether the selected installation can actually reach that repo.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">How to use it</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Start in browser chrome, then move into authoring controls only when the task calls for a write. `Document` tells you what graph is open, `Save target` tells you where the next write goes, and `Access` tells you which installation context Twilite is using. Missing repos are usually installation-scope issues on GitHub, not local-folder issues. The practical procedure lives in the GitHub setup guide.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Current boundaries</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite can classify GitHub destinations as `Writable`, `Accessible`, or `Blocked`, but only `Blocked` is a hard denial. `Accessible` means the installation can reach the repo even if Twilite cannot fully predict the final write outcome. Public browsing does not require the authoring toolbar, while direct commits still do not replace local checkout-aware workflows such as branching, PR preparation, or Actions investigation.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Implementation History</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Archived task graph for the broader GitHub App migration effort behind the current public model.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/archive/github-app/root.node</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Readiness Notes</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The beta board still tracks GitHub App migration as unfinished work behind the scenes.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/beta-readiness/root.node</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Author note</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(245,158,11,0.16);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Annotation</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #d97706, #f59e0b);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">This graph should explain the current GitHub model as it actually exists today: browser-first navigation, explicit save and access state, and paid authoring controls for write workflows. It should stay honest about where local checkout context is still the real authority.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Anchor: boundaries • Author: Michael</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Summary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">GitHub in Twilite is currently a hybrid model: browser-first graph navigation for everyone, authoring and publish controls for signed-in paid users, explicit save targeting inside the app, and local git and gh for checkout-aware work that still lives outside the connector.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Scope: GitHub root</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Initial GitHub Repo Setup</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(124,58,237,0.14);color:#5b21b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Reference</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #8b5cf6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Active task graph for defining the first root/public/private repo structure and browser path model.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Locator: /tasks/github-integration/initial-repo-setup/root.node</div></div></section>",
        "summarySource": "node-updater",
        "updatedAt": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
        "svg": "<svg viewBox=\"0 0 220 160\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\"><rect x=\"24\" y=\"18\" width=\"172\" height=\"124\" rx=\"18\" fill=\"#fffdfa\" stroke=\"#0f172a\" stroke-width=\"5\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"38\" width=\"82\" height=\"14\" rx=\"7\" fill=\"#111827\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"68\" width=\"136\" height=\"16\" rx=\"8\" fill=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke=\"#111827\" stroke-width=\"3\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"96\" width=\"120\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#dbeafe\"/><rect x=\"42\" y=\"118\" width=\"94\" height=\"12\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#e2e8f0\"/></svg>",
        "_classBinding": {
