      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "What you can do today",
        "summary": "Current flows support opening a graph by `github://...`, browsing from the address bar and browser chrome, selecting a concrete installation, repository, branch, and path destination, and saving back through the GitHub App commit route when authoring is enabled. The status surfaces make it easier to tell what document is open, where the next write is pointed, and whether the selected installation can actually reach that repo.",
